    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-14T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/420: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-14T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 14, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 14—-6:58
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Consulate’s 19, January 23, 9 p.m., paragraph 2, and despatch No. 60,
                    political, February 5.<note n="33" xml:id="d700fn33">Despatch not
                        printed.</note> Liberia has informed Secretary General that Council’s
                    pertinent recommendation has been complied with by Liberia’s ratification of
                    Convention on Forced Labor of 1930, Instrument of ratification not yet
                    deposited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
